    ) VALUES (1502944, 'Eslicarbazepine', 'Dicoumarol', 'Moderate', 'Coadministration with eslicarbazepine acetate may decrease the plasma concentrations of S(-) warfarin, the more pharmacologically active of the two enantiomers of warfarin. The mechanism of interaction has not been established. In vitro studies have shown that eslicarbazepine does not significantly affect the plasma protein binding of warfarin.', NULL, 'Given the potential for interaction and the high degree of interpatient variability with respect to warfarin metabolism, patients receiving warfarin should have INR monitored closely during the first 2 to 3 weeks following initiation or discontinuation of eslicarbazepine acetate.', NULL, 'Given the potential for interaction and the high degree of interpatient variability with respect to warfarin metabolism, patients receiving warfarin should have INR monitored closely during the first 2 to 3 weeks following initiation or discontinuation of eslicarbazepine acetate. The same precaution may be applicable during therapy with other similar anticoagulants, although clinical data are lacking. Patients should be advised to seek immediate medical attention if they experience potential signs and symptoms of blood clots such as chest pain, shortness of breath, sudden loss of vision, and pain, redness or swelling in an extremity.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317477);
